    <h2>3. Planetary Mixers: The Versatile All-Rounder</h2>
    <p>The planetary mixer is the most versatile piece of mixing equipment in any bakery. With the right attachments, it can whip egg whites, cream butter and sugar, make cake batter, knead soft doughs, mash potatoes, and grind meat. For bakeries that produce a diverse range of products — cakes, pastries, light doughs, icings, and fillings — a planetary mixer is often more valuable than a spiral mixer.</p>

    <h3>How Planetary Mixers Work</h3>
    <p>The planetary action means the beater attachment orbits the bowl while rotating on its own axis. This ensures every part of the bowl is reached and thoroughly mixed. Three standard attachments come with most commercial planetary mixers:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Wire whisk</strong> — for whipping cream, egg whites, and aerated batters</li>
      <li><strong>Flat beater / paddle</strong> — for cake batters, cookie dough, mashed potatoes, butter creaming</li>
      <li><strong>Dough hook</strong> — for bread and pizza doughs (though spiral is preferred for heavy commercial dough work)</li>
    </ul>

